# Tutorial, chapter 1 — a tiny "people" database.
#
# The `extensional` declaration tells datamog that `person` is a
# base predicate backed by a table; the data comes from the sibling
# `person.csv` (auto-loaded by predicate name).

input predicate person(name: string, country: string, year_born: integer).

# A file runs a single query. This one prints every fact.
?- person(Name, Country, Year).

# To ask a different question, edit the query above (or swap one of these in):
#   ?- person(Name, "uk", Year).      # everyone from the UK
#   ?- person(Name, Country, 1912).   # who was born in 1912
